---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TrustStrip from '../components/TrustStrip.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Floating Cottages Little Boracay Calatagan | Bamboo Cottage Rental"
  description="Rent a floating bamboo cottage at Little Boracay sandbar in Calatagan, Batangas. The signature over-water experience — just hours from Manila."
>
<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="overline">Floating Cottages</span>
    <h1>Little Boracay Floating Cottages</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">The iconic floating bamboo cottages of Little Boracay are one of the most unique and photographed features of any beach destination in Batangas.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<TrustStrip />
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <h2 class="section-title">What Are the Floating Cottages?</h2>
        <p>The <strong>floating bamboo cottages</strong> at Little Boracay are built from native bamboo and nipa palm, anchored directly above the shallow sandbar waters. Unlike traditional beach cottages on land, these structures float over the water — giving visitors the remarkable experience of relaxing, eating, and socialising while surrounded by open sea on all sides.</p>
        <p>The cottages are large enough for groups, featuring a shaded sitting area with easy access to the water. Visitors can step off the edge directly into the shallow, crystal-clear water — one of the most memorable moments of the Little Boracay experience.</p>
        <p>The floating cottage experience is the most popular activity at Little Boracay, and widely considered its defining feature. Many visitors say floating on the cottage, watching the horizon with the water gently moving beneath you, is unlike anything else in the Philippines within driving distance of Manila.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:28px;margin-bottom:16px;">Tips for Enjoying the Floating Cottages</h3>
        <div class="tips-grid">
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">01</div><h4>Book in Advance</h4><p>Floating cottages fill up fast on weekends. Contact us or local operators 2–3 days before your visit.</p></div>
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">02</div><h4>Arrive Early</h4><p>Get to the jump-off point by 7–9 AM to secure your cottage and enjoy the sandbar at low tide.</p></div>
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">03</div><h4>Bring Your Own Food</h4><p>Food service on the sandbar is limited. Pack a cooler with meals and drinks for the day.</p></div>
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">04</div><h4>Protect Your Valuables</h4><p>Bring a waterproof bag or dry box. The cottage floor is above water but splashes happen.</p></div>
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">05</div><h4>Respect the Environment</h4><p>Pack out all trash. Use reef-safe sunscreen to protect the marine ecosystem around the sandbar.</p></div>
          <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-n">06</div><h4>Check Weather &amp; Tides</h4><p>Cottages may be unavailable in rough weather or very high tides. Confirm with operators first.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="fact-table" style="position:sticky;top:80px;">
          <div class="fact-table-header">Cottage Information</div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Material</span><strong>Native bamboo &amp; nipa palm</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Location</span><strong>Anchored over the sandbar</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Capacity</span><strong>Small to large groups</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Water access</span><strong>Step off directly</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Shade</span><strong>Yes — covered sitting area</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Food service</span><strong>Limited — bring your own</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Booking</span><strong>Advance booking recommended</strong></div>
          <div class="fact-row"><span>Availability</span><strong>Weather and tide dependent</strong></div>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-navy" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;margin-top:12px;">Book a Cottage →</a>
        <a href="/visit" class="btn btn-outline" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;margin-top:8px;">Full Travel Guide →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="cta-band">
  <div class="container cta-band-inner">
    <div><h2>Book Your Floating Cottage</h2><p>Secure your spot on the water at Little Boracay sandbar in Calatagan, Batangas.</p></div>
    <div class="cta-actions">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-yellow btn-lg">Book Now</a>
      <a href="/visit" class="btn btn-outline-white btn-lg">Plan Your Visit</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-hero { padding: 60px 0 40px; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(13,43,107,.06), var(--bg)); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
.page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.8rem); font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin: 10px 0 14px; letter-spacing: -.03em; }
.page-lead { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-2); max-width: 620px; line-height: 1.7; }
.two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr; gap: 56px; align-items: start; }
.tips-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; margin-top: 8px; }
.tip-card { padding: 18px; background: var(--bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--r-lg); }
.tip-n { font-size: .68rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: .1em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.tip-card h4 { font-size: .9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 6px; }
.tip-card p { font-size: .84rem; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
@media (max-width: 900px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .tips-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
